📌 Since You Are Using Azure Cosmos DB (Not a Relational Database)

You’re right! Since you are using Azure Cosmos DB and not a relational database (RDBMS like MySQL, PostgreSQL, etc.), JPA annotations like @Entity, @ManyToOne, @OneToMany, @Enumerated, etc., are NOT required.

Cosmos DB is a NoSQL document database, so all data is stored as JSON documents, and there are no relational constraints like foreign keys.

⸻

🚀 Changes Based on Cosmos DB (NoSQL)

✅ ❌ Remove all JPA annotations (@Entity, @Table, @OneToMany, @ManyToOne, etc.)
✅ ✅ Keep only the model fields and Lombok annotations (@Getter, @Setter)
✅ ✅ Use Cosmos DB SDK (@Container, @PartitionKey) instead of JPA annotations

